<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Agrarian Legacy</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 40px;
            line-height: 1.6;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
        }
        .container {
            max-width: 900px;
            margin: auto;
            background: white;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0px 0px 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }
        h1, h2 {
            color: #9d2f2b;
            text-align: center;
        }
        .section {
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            gap: 20px;
        }
        .section:nth-child(even) {
            flex-direction: row-reverse;
        }
        .section img {
            width: 45%;
            height: auto;
            border-radius: 10px;
            border: 3px solid #8a1d1d;
        }
        .text {
            width: 50%;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Agrarian Legacy</h1>
        <div class="section">
            <img src="/images/agrarian-legacy.jpeg" alt="Agrarian Legacy">
            <div class="text">
                <p><strong>Definition:</strong> Agrarian legacy refers to the historical, cultural, and economic influences that agricultural practices have left on societies over time.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <h2>Key Aspects of Agrarian Legacy</h2>
        <div class="section">
            <img src="/images/download.jpeg" alt="Historical Impact">
            <div class="text">
                <h3>Historical Impact</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Early civilizations like Mesopotamia, Egypt, and the Indus Valley thrived due to agriculture.</li>
                    <li>Farming led to permanent human settlements and social hierarchies.</li>
                    <li>Feudal systems revolved around land ownership.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <img src="/images/tom.png" alt="Cultural Influence">
            <div class="text">
                <h3>Cultural Influence</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Festivals and traditions often revolve around farming cycles.</li>
                    <li>Folk music, art, and literature depict agrarian life.</li>
                    <li>Indigenous knowledge of irrigation and farming has been passed down for generations.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <img src="/images/fbvfbdb.webp" alt="Economic Contributions">
            <div class="text">
                <h3>Economic Contributions</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Agriculture was the backbone of early and medieval economies.</li>
                    <li>The Green Revolution boosted food production and economic growth.</li>
                    <li>Agribusiness continues to play a vital role in modern economies.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <img src="/images/technological-developments.jpeg" alt="Technological Developments">
            <div class="text">
                <h3>Technological and Scientific Developments</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Irrigation systems and crop rotation improved productivity.</li>
                    <li>Mechanization transformed farming methods.</li>
                    <li>Biotechnology enhanced crop resilience and yield.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <img src="/images/land-ownership.jpeg" alt="Land Ownership and Social Structure">
            <div class="text">
                <h3>Land Ownership and Social Structure</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Feudal and zamindari systems controlled vast agricultural lands.</li>
                    <li>Land reforms aimed at equitable distribution.</li>
                    <li>Rural-urban migration has impacted agrarian communities.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <img src="/images/enviromental-considerations.jpeg" alt="Environmental Considerations">
            <div class="text">
                <h3>Environmental Considerations</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Traditional farming relied on sustainable organic techniques.</li>
                    <li>Modern industrial farming caused soil degradation and deforestation.</li>
                    <li>Organic farming and permaculture are gaining prominence.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

        <h2>Challenges to Agrarian Legacy in the Modern Era</h2>
        <div class="section">
            <div class="text-center">
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Urbanization:</strong> Reduction of farmland due to city expansion.</li>
                    <li><strong>Climate Change:</strong> Unpredictable weather affecting agriculture.</li>
                    <li><strong>Technological Disparities:</strong> Limited access to modern farming tools for small-scale farmers.</li>
                    <li><strong>Market Pressures:</strong> Global trade policies affecting traditional farming.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

        <h2>Conclusion</h2>
        <div class="section">
            <div class="text-center">
                <p>Agrarian legacy has shaped economies, cultures, and societies throughout history. While advancements have transformed agriculture, preserving traditional knowledge and promoting sustainable farming practices remain crucial for the future.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
